abstract: Our readers, (says the Armaugh Gnaradian.) know as a matter of history that several ships belenging to the Spanish Armada, destined for the conquest of England, were driven away by storm to the West coast of Ireland and wrecked. abstract: To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times: These women are always grumbling. We unfortunate men have to abide the infliction of mental three-legged stools and hide our diminished heads,--all because there is so much talk about Woman's Rights and her Wrongs. Heaven knows the men have wrongs too, only they are so modest they do not blazon them forth like the "fair" sex. Woman's prerogative is to govern mankind.

abstract: BROADWAY.--Mrs. MOWATT played Ion last evening, to a large audience. The performance was far better than on its first representation. Mrs. M. is fast recovering her natural voice, and the difference in her acting is plainly observable. She does not appear to labor so much, and their is less of the ranting, which we have heretofore noticed as so objectionable in an actress. She was warmly applauded and is certainly growing in public favor.

abstract: FATAL RAILROAD ACCIDANT.--Tuesday evening, at 6 o'clock, near Elizabethtown, a man named STEVENSON was run down by the Philadelphia train and killed instantly. abstract: THE BROADWAY.--The new play of "Anne Blake," was repeated last evening. Anne, the heroine, is left a dependent upon a sordid Uncle, who seeks by marrying her to a rich heir to a peerage, to release the mortgages upon his estate, held by the proposed husband.

abstract: Aunt Deborah was a good philosopher, as the world goes ; that is, she had a theory, according to which she practiced, never worrying herself much about its truth. Her doctrine was that everybody has got to commit a thousand blunders in this world, and so, every time she committed one, she rejoiced at being rid of one more source of vexation and trouble.

abstract: Yesterday morning, the Schooner Gazette, Capt. BASSETT, reached Cleveland harbor in distress, having suffered much in the gales of last week on the Lake.
